{"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Divider"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Divider\/geometryGroup()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"geometryGroup"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default OpenSwiftUI views push position and size changes down"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"through the view hierarchy, so that only views that draw"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"something (known as leaf views) apply the current animation to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their frame rectangle. However in some cases this coalescing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior can give undesirable results; inserting a geometry"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group can correct that. A group acts as a barrier between the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view and its subviews, forcing the position and size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"values to be resolved and animated by the parent, before being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"passed down to each subview."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The example below shows one use of this function: ensuring that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the member views of each row in the stack apply (and animate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as) a single geometric transform from their ancestor view,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rather than letting the effects of the ancestor views be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied separately to each leaf view. If the members of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"ItemView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" may be added and removed at different times the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"group ensures that they stay locked together as animations are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applied."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["VStack {","    ForEach(items) { item in","        ItemView(item: item)","            .geometryGroup()","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns: a new view whose geometry is isolated from that of its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent view."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/divider\/geometrygroup()"]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE13geometryGroupQryF::SYNTHESIZED::s:11OpenSwiftUI7DividerV","role":"symbol","platforms":[{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","unavailable":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","unavailable":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","unavailable":false},{"deprecated":false,"beta":false,"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","unavailable":false}],"title":"geometryGroup()","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"symbolKind":"method","remoteSource":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/OpenSwiftUIProject\/OpenSwiftUI\/blob\/main\/Sources\/OpenSwiftUICore\/Render\/RendererEffect\/RendererEffect.swift#L294","fileName":"RendererEffect.swift"},"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore"},"references":{"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui","type":"topic","title":"OpenSwiftUI","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Declare the user interface and behavior for your app on every platform."}]},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/View":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"View","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"View","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A type that represents part of your app’s user interface and provides"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"modifiers that you use to configure views."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/view","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View","role":"symbol"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Divider/geometryGroup()":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"geometryGroup","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP"}],"title":"geometryGroup()","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Isolates the geometry (e.g. position and size) of the view"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from its parent view."}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/divider\/geometrygroup()","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Divider\/geometryGroup()"},"doc://OpenSwiftUI/documentation/OpenSwiftUI/Divider":{"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Divider","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/openswiftui\/divider","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A visual element that can be used to separate other content."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Divider","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Divider","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Divider","role":"symbol"}}}